Palestinian children, women, and men are living in extremely difficult conditions due to ongoing armed conflict and intense military operations. According to reports, approximately 25,000 people have been killed, 70% of them women and children, and over 61,500 have been injured, while thousands remain trapped under rubble. People in Gaza suffer from severe shortages of food, water, and medicine, along with a communications blackout that exacerbates confusion and fear. Schools and hospitals have been heavily damaged, making access to healthcare and education extremely difficult. The United Nations and other humanitarian organizations are striving to provide essential aid, but the blockade and conflict make these efforts challenging to implement.
